---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const updated = 'July 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — PromoStrats"
  description="The terms that apply when you engage PromoStrats for Shopify design and SEO work."
>
  <div class="ps2-legal">
    <div class="ps2-wrap">
      <span class="ps2-eyebrow">// legal</span>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="ps2-legal-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <div class="ps2-legal-body">
        <p>
          These terms apply to Shopify design, SEO and related services provided by PromoStrats ("I", "me") to you (the
          "client"). By engaging me for work, you agree to them. Specific projects may also have their own written
          quote or proposal, which takes precedence where it differs from these general terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Scope of work</h2>
        <p>
          Before any paid work begins, I'll set out what's included, the price, and rough timescales in writing. Work
          outside that agreed scope may be quoted separately. I don't start chargeable work until the scope and price
          are confirmed by you.
        </p>

        <h2>Quotes &amp; pricing</h2>
        <p>
          Prices are quoted clearly before work starts and are valid for the period stated in the quote. Unless stated
          otherwise, quotes exclude third-party costs such as apps, themes, fonts, or hosting, which are your
          responsibility.
        </p>

        <h2>Payment</h2>
        <p>
          Payment terms are set out in your quote or invoice. Larger projects may require a deposit before work begins,
          with the balance due on completion. Invoices are payable by the date shown on the invoice.
        </p>

        <h2>Client responsibilities</h2>
        <p>
          To deliver the work, I'll need timely access to your Shopify store and any relevant accounts, plus content,
          images, and feedback when requested. Delays in providing these may affect timelines. You confirm you have the
          right to use any materials you supply to me.
        </p>

        <h2>Revisions &amp; approval</h2>
        <p>
          Each project includes a reasonable number of revisions as described in your quote. Once work is approved or
          published, further changes may be treated as new work and quoted accordingly.
        </p>

        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          On full payment, ownership of the final deliverables created specifically for you transfers to you.
          Third-party components (themes, apps, fonts, plugins) remain subject to their own licences. I may reference the
          finished work in my portfolio unless you ask me in writing not to.
        </p>

        <h2>Liability</h2>
        <p>
          I take care to do good work, but I can't guarantee specific commercial outcomes such as particular search
          rankings, traffic levels, or sales, as these depend on factors outside my control. To the extent permitted by
          law, my liability for any project is limited to the fees you paid for that project.
        </p>

        <h2>Cancellation</h2>
        <p>
          Either of us may end an engagement in writing. If you cancel part-way through, you're responsible for payment
          for work completed up to that point.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales.</p>

        <p class="ps2-legal-note">
          Note: this is a starting template, not legal advice. Adjust it to match how you actually work — and have it
          reviewed by someone qualified — before relying on it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .ps2-legal {
    padding: 72px 0 96px;
  }

  .ps2-legal h1 {
    font-family: var(--ps2-disp);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: clamp(34px, 4.4vw, 52px);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.04;
    margin-top: 18px;
    color: var(--ps2-ink);
  }

  .ps2-legal-updated {
    margin-top: 14px;
    font-family: var(--ps2-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ps2-ink-soft);
  }

  .ps2-legal-body {
    max-width: 68ch;
    margin-top: 40px;
  }

  .ps2-legal-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--ps2-disp);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 22px;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--ps2-ink);
    margin-top: 40px;
  }

  .ps2-legal-body p {
    margin-top: 14px;
    color: var(--ps2-ink-soft);
    font-size: 16.5px;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .ps2-legal-body a {
    color: var(--ps2-cobalt);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .ps2-legal-body a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .ps2-legal-note {
    margin-top: 40px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--ps2-line);
    font-family: var(--ps2-mono);
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: var(--ps2-ink-soft);
    background: #fff;
  }
</style>
